An attack by Al-Shabaab militants at Kenya’s Garissa University claimed the lives of 147 people on Thursday. The four Islamic gunmen who who held hostages and killed university students were killed by security forces to end the siege. Plans are now underway to evacuate the remaining students and others from the area, according to Kenya\'s National Disaster Operation Centre. We look at the story on the Lip News with Mark Sovel and John Fenoglio.

