Moi university Garissa Campus has officially reopened nine months after an Al Shabaab terror attack at the institution that saw more than 147 people mostly students losing their lives the campus that is the only one of its kind in North Eastern Kenya, reopened its gates Monday with both teaching and non teaching staff reporting back to the heavily fortified place of work and as Hassan Mugambi reports security measures put in place at the institution include, a 25 man police post established in the institution  and a 230 million shilling perimeter wall to be constructed....
